<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 9:47AM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern
Washington...southwestern Beaver and western Iron Counties through
1030 AM MDT...
At 947 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 20 miles east of Ranch Campground to 9 miles
north of New Harmony. Movement was north at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Newcastle, Lund, Hamlin Valley, Indian Peak Management Range and
Woods Reservoir.
This includes Utah Route 56 between mile markers 30 and 49.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
